1
00:00:00,075 --> 00:00:04,275
Inheritance in JavaScript classes allows one class to extend another

2
00:00:04,688 --> 00:00:08,950
enabling the use of existing code and creating hierarchies of classes

3
00:00:09,338 --> 00:00:17,413
The 'extends' keyword is used to signify inheritance and the 'super' keyword is utilized to call functions on an object's parent class

4
00:00:17,800 --> 00:00:26,325
This approach to inheritance enhances reusability and maintainability by allowing common functionalities to be shared across classes

